76561198058075059,Recommended,256290,28571553,"Posted: 23 December, 2016",all,baal_zevul,"As a whole, I think my opinion of Child of Light is somewhat mixed. The gameplay was rewarding and motivating, giving enough complexity to pique the curiosity of a player like myself but not so much as to confuse or discourage me - and indeed, the basic movement and combat in the game was whimsical and pleasant. The world and character design go to this, encouraging the player to explore the world. Ultimately, I think my dissapointment comes down to the writing, and the fundamental inability of the mechanics to sufficiently motivate through the game as a whole.While for the most part the plot and characters are quite charming and interesting, I think their simplicity is ultimately a drawback. While some characters experience adequate arcs, in other respects I thought the reliance on genre staples, or in other words tropes, made the story and characters feel stale or undersubstantiated. In particular certain turns for characters or turns of the story left me rolling my eyes or feeling somewhat dissappointed with the games inability to achieve reconciliation, or adequately build and progress character motivations and relationships to make conflicts that felt nuanced or resolutions that felt truly cathartic and enlightening. Ultimately that may come across as a disporportionate criticism of the game for what is in the end not the whole of its construction, but I do believe we have here a story that, despite its simplicity, wants to have an arc and have themes and learning, and in that sense I believe it falls a little short.Despite this, I would like to again highlight the charm of the game. Moments like gaining the ability of flight really capture the sense of whimsy, fun, and fantasy the whole game goes towards. That I would say is its biggest success.So, in short, Child of Light is a beautiful game with fun and nuanced yet not overly complicated mechanics and a charming, emotive story that as a whole feels somewhat flat and underwhelming. Still, I do not regret playing it and would recommend it to fans of the genre."
