76561198269588665,Not Recommended,256290,31846802,Posted: 19 May,all,rubypond,"I can kind of understand why everyone is sooooo in love with this game. The graphics are amazingly beautiful, the soundscape is marvellous and there is a pretty little story going on. Oh yes, I heard so many positive reviews about this game – basically everybody is enchanted by it! But I am not.As a player, I do like lovely art in a game and of course a good score brings it to life. In this game all this just was wasted: the gameplay itself was so boring that I didn’t enjoy exploring the beautiful world after the first hour or so. You just basically walk (and later fly) around pretty aimlessly. You can find treasures, carry out little quests and do some fighting alongside the main storyline. And the fights were the worst, because they were painfully manual and boring. Same thing over and over again. Thank god you didn’t actually have to fight that much if you didn’t want to. Because oh yes, there were battles everywhere.Usually I’m all for exploring and doing all the quests and finding all the items. This time I just wanted the experience to end as fast as possible. This time I didn’t do all the side quests and didn’t find all the items and didn’t fight almost any battles. I just didn’t want to bother. I’m sad to admit this, because this game had so much potential.Let’s talk about the music. It fit perfectly well to the game world. It was as pretty as the graphics in the game, it created lovely atmosphere. Piano and violin sounded so beautiful in the score. But it was getting very repetitive: after some time you just got very numb about it. It didn’t offer anything suprising or new. The same thing just went on and on and on… And the same thing you could say about the whole game.So, in conclusion. I do understand why so many are enchanted by this. It has a good combo of things and it is not a game with horrible quality. Sadly this just wasn’t a game for me. For me this game was just plain 