,Recommended,256290,34006023,Posted: 3 August,all,Pakkidis,"Rating: 7.5/10Overview: 2D Turn Based RPGThe Good:+ Water colored art style+ Interesting cast of characters, each character has 3 skill trees+ I enjoyed the combat system. Every character and enemy take turns attacking indicated by a timeline. Attacking enemies when they are near the end of the timeline will set them further back potentially giving you more time to attack. You can freely switch party members in combat utilizing different set of skills.+ Simplistic crafting system allowing you to slot gems into three categories altering certain stats.+ Great soundtrackThe Average:+/- The story is a light-hearted fantasy told through rhyming and the rhymes are bad making it that much harder to care about the story.+/- Combat does feel repetitive after awhile, once you understand the basic mechanics of the game not much changes afterwards.+/- I felt there was very little build up in the climax or the story leading to what I consider a rather abrupt end, this is potentially due to a weak story.Conclusion:Like every other turn based RPG your mileage will vary depending on how much you like the combat system. This is a rather light-hearted fantasy RPG that will last approximately 10 hours depending on skill level."
