,Recommended,256290,15608868,"Posted: 29 April, 2015",all,ADD ME FOR GWENT,"First and foremost, WOW. I was rather skeptical when I got this game, not sure if I will enjoy a turn-based RPG as I normally play action/ FPS. But since this game had Overwhelmingly Positive reviews, and the fact that I could get it cheap, I decided to give it a try.I was pretty thorough with my play-through and clocked a total of 13.7 hours. And the thing is, I enjoyed every moment of it. I didn't complete it in one sitting (obviously) but I think it was three. I kept playing on and on and I think part of the reason was the battles. As mentioned, it is turn-based RPG with a focus on a timeline (some mentioned that the Final Fantasy series use this mechanic, but I'm new to it). There is no guarantee that you can even cast your spell, and sometimes you even lose the fight having done completely no action. There is some strategy involved and fights can be frustrating especially in Hard mode. It was new for me and I really liked it.Apart from the battle system, there is also the crafting system worth mentioning. You collect these sorta gems from chests or from battle drops and you can combine them to form more refined versions or hybrid versions. For example, ruby + sapphire + emerald = diamond ; and 3 x ruby = bigger ruby. Equipping these gems in different slots give different stats that can help you in the battle.The story is fine, nothing spectacular/ mind-blowing like in Bioshock Infinite, but it flows smoothly just like a Disney classic. The artwork is really well done too.I really enjoyed this game, and I look forward to upcoming games of this genre.10/10"
