alingi. Illumination9. The Bells in the Capilli VillageI love it. If you fly into the bells, the bells jingle.10. MusicThe piano accompaniement is so soothing and beautiful. Kudos to the composer.11. CharactersRubella - Jester HealerGolem - Ancient GolemFinn - Capelli MageNorah - Swift Fighter (Betrays you)Aurora - Leader UnitRobert - Mouse ArcherGem - SorceressOengus - FighterTristin - Better copy of RubellaCONS1. Contact Points between the FloorsBefore you get Flying, sometimes just up onto a second level is extremely difficult.2. DLCA lot of the game is DLC-based. But I'll let it slide because the game is amazing.3. 2 Character Combat2 is kind of a few. It would be better with 3.4. Repeated MonstersAlthough there are many uniques monsters, you will find repeats where monsters just change colour from green to red to blue to black. There is also a case of changing monsters from from a live version to a zombie version, but I like this one.Total number of uniques area. Boar manb. Ogrec. Spike dogd. Needle nose flyere. Ghost Horsef. Alligator guard (Has a Zombie version)g. Bird guardh. Spirit of Deathi. Leaf insectj. Centaur ArcherSUGGESTIONS1. Ailment ListCould you provide a hot tip to show what the ailments mean? I had to guess that paralyze was you could move on the action bar.2. Igniculusa. Distracting large and dangerous enemiesb. Uncovering hidden symbols which can't be seem unless illuminatedc. Getting eaten by a large beast.3. MultiplayerI'm actually wondering if you could split the heroes and Igniculus on an online battle.4. More Monster Slots + Hero SlotsI would like to see a 3 v 7 battle. Like the 3 heroes being surrounded. Just like Final Fantasy."
