,Recommended,256290,10827729,"Posted: 26 June, 2014",all,rapid squat clapping,"If you're thinking about it, do it. It's a very simple JRPG- linear story/path- 8 Characters + DLC with 3 Skill trees each and set ""classes""/niches- turned based battle, 2 party vs. 3 monster with time bar thing for turns- very simple, still very customizable augmenting- minimal inventory management (just pots)but it's very ""open"" in the sense that there's no waypoints, minimaps, or directions. Usually there's only one way to go, but you stay in very big maps that are kinda easy to get lost in. Hidden treasures are plenty.Most of the difficulty is in battles. You get a little sprite/Navi like thing for your mouse (kinda like Super Mario Galaxy) that opens chests, does puzzles, and ""stuns"" enemies so touching them won't trigger a battle on the map. In battle, you use it to slow (a single) enemy, and heal yourself. He has his own energy bar. This, along with being able to rotate party members instantly during battle + gem customization + timing your actions to cause interrupts (attacking an enemy during the red part of the bar) means if you're good enough you can do fights without every getting attacked.Higher skillcap than an average JRPG fight, much more active.Art and music are beautiful and probably worth the game alone. The script is very childish. Everything rhymes (it's kinda cute), very poetic. Sometimes a little cheesy, in a funny way.Story reminds me a little of Bastion - where you're curious as to what happened and the characters all have backgrounds that make you want to learn more, but this game's not the most story driven.Just good combat, very engaging but not stressful play, and a relaxing artstyle.Do it.The only downside really is that you need UPlay. Glhf awful game.Actual annoying parts though - while there's saveslots, there's also no save button and it's all autosave. I'm a save every 30 seconds kinda guy so it bugs me a little. But it autosaves really often (there's a spinning circle in the bottom right). Also, it's hard to gauge a sense of progress. There's a worldmap, but it only shows places you've been to and you don't really know where they are). The game is subdivided into Chapters but I don't know how many there are.DLC is okay - I don't really like the skins. Haven't done the character one yet though."
