76561198044437800,Recommended,256290,10589126,"Posted: 20 June, 2014",all,zealousduck,"This game is a lot of things... but in a word: Delightful.I went in to this game expecting it to be an easy, story-driven game. After all, the poetic dialogue and beautiful artwork do a lot to give the impression of a casual, almost-childish game.What I did not expect was a refreshingly new (and actually somewhat difficult) combat system. Of all the RPGs I've played, the battle system in Child of Light is one of my favorites. Admittedly, the remaining RPG elements are simplified: Stats are gained solely through levels and stat-pumping items, and each character has 3 armor ""slots"" for various gems. The customization is a little limited in that respect, but I think that to be appropriate given the semi-casual nature of the game.Of course, there's an easy mode (which I do NOT recommend) for those who just want the story.tl;dr - Good artwork, music, nice spin on RPG gameplay, 4.5/5. Would recommend."
