76561198104120145,Recommended,256290,10035971,"Posted: 6 May, 2014",all,jd5team,"I honestly really enjoy this game. The beginning is a little annoying when you are getting used to the controls and the timing (everything seems to move in slow motion due to ""dream world"") but after a while its no problem. There are a ton of really awesome mechanics that make the game more fun and not a run of the mill turn based game. Combat has a timing element, with a window for ""casting"" (basically when your preparing your attack) and you can interupt enemies while they are casting which essentially skips them. You can slow down your enemies with your firefly companion so you can skip ahead of them. There are also attack types like in pokemon with light being strong against dark, water against fire, etc. that adds to the mix. Overall, for the price, I would say this game is really good. Something that gets old is the constant rhyming in dialogue, but thats just my opinion. It does not ruin the game, it just gets on my nerves. I would say the depth of story and the cool mechanics more than compensates for annoying dialogue. Overall I'd give it 8.5/10"
