,Not Recommended,256290,18734988,"Posted: 28 October, 2015",all,Spider3,"***Note: Negative review is for rpg turn-based mechanics lover. If you are just looking for a light rpg experience with platform elements with beautiful gfx, certainly this game is for you. Otherwise for deep turn based mechanics rpg, better look elsewhere ***I would like to give thumbs up for Child of Light, also because I was really looking forward to play it.But as big turn-based rpgs fan, I really can't upvote it.Before I get flamed for my negative reviews: the game itself is not that bad, the graphic is just so amazing, the soundtrack beuatiful and enchanting. The story was also good enough so far.But if after 6 hours I don't feel any kind of addiction of going on, something is wrong.And the problems are the mechanics. The platform elements are ok, but the turn-based ones are definitely not enough and too much repetitive. I am playing in ""expert"" mode and everything got after 2-3 hours too boring and repetitive. I've nothing abount grinding (thing that is not really required in this game) when the story keeps pushing you to continue because you want to know more, but this is not the case - too long intervals between exploration and story continues. I never used an item except on the third boss (and I was plenty of pots). The creatures are too similar and predictable (weakness to element). And party of 2 persons (even if you can switch them) is  limiting too much the field choices. So far the only thing I did was casting a spell, melee attack with the other, and replace with healer as needed.I'm very sorry but I am going to abandon it for now. It's really a shame and an hard decision because the graphic is such a pleasure for the eyes. Shame."
