,Recommended,256290,13396138,"Posted: 15 December, 2014",all,Shinobi Magi,"Child of Light was everything I was hoping it to be, it was immersive, it was gorgeous, and above all, it had a phenomenal soundtrack.Child of Light tries something fun with it storytelling by having the characters rhyme whenever they talk. It's not for everyone but I was rather fond of it. It made the game feel like a fairy tale come alive.The exploration of the world is fun and exciting, the first level of the game sets you up for what to expect throughout the rest of the world, and I have to say, it's never disappointing. Treasure hunting rarely feels like a chore and the ways to obtain certain treasure feels refreshing and uncomplicated.In terms of combat Child of Light takes a page from the classic rpg format of turn based fighting and adds several implements. This makes the turn based fighting immersive and exciting and with the allies you come across you will find many unique and interesting ways to topple the competition. There is also a gearing system involving gem stones, I've barely scratched the surface on this and I gotta say, the upgrades you choose through this system really play a part in combat.My only real gripe with child of light is how short the game feels. When the game comes to the end you feel like you could've used more time to grind your allies and discovered more quests/treasure. I guess I'll check out the dlc and story plus and see if that doesn't change my mind.Child of Light is a must play for RPG and fantasy enthusiasts."
