,Recommended,256290,26578261,"Posted: 13 November, 2016",all,ThePCGamer101,"DISCLAIMER: This is a full review, and NOT a first impressions review like all my other reviews, if you want a better full review, then please read better reviews then mineChild of Light is a beautiful RPG game developed and published by Ubisoft. From start to finish it shows a solid gameplay, a vibrant world, and a quite interesting story with more than a few twists.Sound design is amazing, and graphically speaking, the game looks magnificent, and everytime you reach a new place, you find yourself looking at every place of the screen, mindblowing designs and drawings that are taken out of a fairy tale, beautiful. The magic of the game is greatly resembled too, and it's one of the strongest points in the game.The amount of hours might look short for an RPG, but it's not really short clocking in at around 10-11 hours in total. The game doesn't drag on, some battles are indeed hard but can be overtaken by strategy, the story from start to finish feels good, like reading a book. It's all fun from start to finish, and at the end you feel realized and full because it doesn't leave you wanting for more like some other gamesThe gameplay is a turn-based fighting RPG, which is fast, there's no long animations and it's really fun thanks to constantly being in motion, you will be using characters in the fight that you can swap at any time, there are quite a few characters. They of course level up, and you'll have to see what's the best course of action regarding their skills. I want to mention that it's very fun to move as the protagonist too, specially with the amount of secrets that are everywhere! Nothing falls short in the gameplay portion of the game!I love the fact that the story is told in rhyme which adds a lovely touch to the game. Overall, Child of Light is a game that offers a great time guaranteed for RPG players, you can't really go wrong with this game. Shame about the forced DRM of Uplay but it's Ubisoft, what do you expect?RECOMMENDED :)Also, best to play with a controller"
