,Recommended,256290,26671814,"Posted: 18 November, 2016",all,I'm Not Sue,"I found this to be a solid and charming RPG.  Dont let the ubisoft brand fool you.  I played for a bit over 18 hrs and enjoyed this game quite a bit.The gameplay is, if anything, a bit too easy in the same way that Kingdom Hearts is.  If you are modestly competent almost every fight wont be challenging even at the harder difficulty setting, but it's still enjoyable to play.  Combat is similar to an ATB system with actions being queued up on a time bar before being performed.  Some actions can be interrupted, others affect a characters turn in some way, allowing for some finesse and control on the part of the player.  This comes along with an ATB-independent heal the player can perform with his mouse cursor that uses its own slowly recharging resource, and for some reason I found the balance between the two fairly enjoyable and engaging.  In the more tense fights, healing characters at the right moments was crucial along with timing when you would be able to heal again after expending all of your resource was fairly important.  Characters are diverse and can fit varied roles in combat, enough that I didnt feel like I should stick to just a few that I might like.  Outside of combat puzzles are fairly easy and nothing too complex or ingenious comes up, and there is some light exploration and backtracking for rewards you can do as well.  Exploration does kind of fall flat a little because they give you complete exploration powers very shortly into the game, but its also not a metroidvania title so calling it a 'missed opportunity' or like doesn't quite fit.  Jamming RPG, light crafting mechanics, skill trees, exploration, etc all into a game is a lot and eventually you'd end up with feature bloat.The story has a kind of light fairytail whimsy to it, in the way that some aspects are obscured or ambiguous or mean to be accepted prima facie.  It works out for the most part, and the way they presented the world and characters was satisfying.  and had some nice twists too. Some people dont like the rhyming dialogue, but I did.  I liked most all of the characters too, even a few I expected not to on first glance like Rubella.  I think if anything one of the problems they had was the sin of taking away a character from the player whom one might have expended permanent stat upgrade consumables on, and also in introducing one character too late and letting a few others kind of flounder a bit.  Still, the ones that did get time in the story were nice.I'd highly recommend it, it's not a top 5 title but it definitely went into my favorites."
