76561198068493036,Recommended,256290,13222429,"Posted: 3 December, 2014",all,[C-137] NoopNoop,You know that feel you get after watching the very last episode of your favorite show? This is that feel11/10 I'm feeling so hard right now :(
76561198091551735,Recommended,256290,13241790,"Posted: 5 December, 2014",all,Liandra,"Child of Light is abeautifulgame. The art has a lovely watercolor look that adds to the fairytale feel. The music is really well done, too - evocative, supporting but never overpowering the action. However, the story is short and to reiterate, it is afairytale, so if you want an epic campaign to save the world, this isn't it. This is a story about a child growing up, learning to become a leader, how to deal with loss and betrayal, and how to be everything she needs to be - strong, caring, gentle, noble, and powerful.One of the strongest points of Child of Light is the combat system - there are about four to six things you have to keep track of simultaneously, and it gets crazy. The real-time turn-based combat was immensely fun - you can only battle with two of your party members at a time, and often the enemy has three combatants that attack at different moments and at different speeds. Learning to control the firefly and shift your party members in and out of the fight in order to combo-stunlock the enemy is a wonderful challenge that really never gets old.I really enjoyed the diversity of characters here. They come in all shapes and ages and sizes, and all the characters become strong, with their own motivations and stories. In one case, it's a girl being strong for her depressed brother. In another, it's an orphan out for vengeance on the people who killed her parents. There's a mage out to prove himself to his elders. A disgraced warrior out to restore his honor. A boy who wants to win a fair lady's heart. Major points for not sexualizing the female characters, especially as two of them are about 7-10 years old.You can't customize your characters' weapons/armor. You can change the stones attached (called Oculi in the game) to add different stats, but you have the same weapons throughout the game and there are no shops and there is no currency. The Oculi are pretty strong - there's the usual RPG combining and there are other stat boosts in the game, but overall customization stays relatively simple.Perhaps the weakest part of the game is the dialogue - I personally liked it most of the time, but I agree with other reviewers that sometimes clarity is sacrificed for the sake of rhyme. If you hate Shakespeare and can't stand poetry, this game is not for you. The rhyming dialogue gives a sometimes immersive, other times jarring feel - when it works, it's hilarious. When it doesn't, it's just plain bad.tl;dr:Pros: beautiful art & music, great combat system, short and fairly casual storyline, wonderful cast of charactersCons: dialogue is hot or cold, game is relatively short, limited customization"
