76561198058631844,Recommended,256290,12505457,"Posted: 15 October, 2014",all,*OCB* BavMotWork,"I finished this game and that's really saying something.  I usually lose interest eventually and don't finish.  This one has that perfect balance to where it kept me entertained and interested enough to continue playing, but didn't make me dedicate too much as far as time and patience.  I recommend it for gamers like myself who prefer less depth on occasion for the sake of being able to jump in and play it for an hour or two after work.  Here are a few pros and cons because I'm not much of a composer.+Beautiful artwork+Fast paced yet turn based combat that's entertaining enough to make you want more+Lots of secret loot to find+Crafting is very simple but effective+Character progression is well-balanced+Diverse characters with lots of different skills+Ease of travel+Shallow story for shallow folks+Short and sweet+Reasonably priced, especially at the 60% off discount-Poetic dialogue is pretty cheesy, but I get it-Potions are a bit useless unless you're in a dire situation-Could have used a little more difficulty in combat, just a littleI give it an 8/10, if they ever make a second one, I will insta-buy.P.S.  I should also say that Uplay is not a big deal in any shape or form.  I see a lot of people freaking out over it, but they're just being dramatic pansies.  In the 24 hours it took me to beat this, I saw the Uplay screen a total of about 60 seconds. It never once interfered with anything at all.  Also, if it prevents piracy, I'm all for it.  Get a job and buy your games, people work hard on them."
