76561197985881367,Recommended,256290,13314004,"Posted: 10 December, 2014",all,Lucius Brimstone,"This is probably the most negative review for Child of Light that you'll read, but I honestly wasn't blown away by it.  Still, it's probably worth checking out.  I'd wait until it's on sale for around 5 dollars.It's fine.  It's alright.  It's a fairly standard RPG so there really isn't a lot of gameplay going on.  There isn't a lot of variety in the music.  The artwork is good but the animations are creepy at times.On the plus side the combat/outside of combat has a really cool thing going on with the support character, who can freeze enemies outside of combat, slow them down inside of combat and heal you in either situation.  His operations are independent of the other characters/time line that combat follows so that part is neat.  CoL also has a sort of Mario RPG esque feel to it's combat since it's centered around timing your attacks effectively to interrupt the enemy's.There's a story and it's not the worst but it's sort of dull.  Very fairy tale inspired, and that part of it is cool, but it's definitely not the sort of story meant to last the 6-8 hours of gameplay.  It's not bad by any means but I think it could have been utilized better in another game type.One of the bigger draws is the writing, which is clever in a lot of parts but I think that it ultimately loses out by the game not having voice work for the characters.  Oh, the narrator bits between major segments are fantastic and the writing really comes alive then, but everywhere else it's just kind of meh.  There are great points to it, and I did enjoy the interactions between characters, but well, it felt lacking in some regard.  It felt like the writing was trying to elevate itself in some way but the author's skill wasn't there.  At times the rhyming style seemed to detract from the actual writing.  Pity, that.Oh, watch out by the way.  The difficulty curve in Child of Light is crazy.  You'll go from no challenge to extremely difficult bosses near the mid/end, which will then peter out into pretty easy fights by the very end.I've read that the game itself is short or feels rushed but despite my claims that the story feels stretched, the game itself seemed to pace itself pretty well.  I thought it was about the right length.I recommend Child of Light but this is a case of a game that I don't think should have been a game.  The non-game parts are still good, if pretentious.  Ehh.Oh, Child of Light also has the absolute worst DLC I've ever seen in a game.  Sure, one is a new character, but two more are main character reskins and the rest are item packs.  These item packs are of items that exist in the game already and are acquired pretty frequently so I'm not really sure why the DLC exists.  Oh, wait.  Money."
