,Recommended,256290,24845309,"Posted: 12 August, 2016",all,The Ryan,"It's a good game in the JRPG style without the Japenese elements to it (anime, hyperbole, etc.).  Though the ending felt a bit rushed, the game was enjoyable throughout.  There are a lot of ways to approach battles, many different tactics depending on which characters to want to use, so there may be some replayability for those endeavoring to experiment.  Character progression relies on players making choices of which stats to boost and which abilities to learn, which I think is a great mechanic that many modern JRPGs have gotten away from.  You can level these characters to suit your style, and you're not just filling spheres on a skill tree without branches.The rhyming dialogue is interesting, bouncing between clever and annoying at times, but overall I think it's a success.  I'd recommend for anyone who enjoys RPGs with turn-based battles.  It's not a very difficult game, and there's plenty of side stuff to do if you go looking for it."
