76561198121113370,Recommended,256290,9982835,"Posted: 30 April, 2014",all,Aeternum Horizon,"""What's inside? Homicide!""Child of Light is a surprisingly fun RPG that's basically a modernized spin on the fairy tail storytelling genre. Everything looks, sounds, and feels fantastical and artistic, from the oil painting-esque graphics to the poetic dialogue, this game is definitely worth more than the $14.99 price tag.There's several classic RPG elements here: characters level up, you get allies that fill up all sorts of roles, a skill tree, collectibles, crafting system, and turn based combat. In terms of the last one though, Child of Light gives a new spin on the old turn based combat formula: instead of having a set order, you have a waiting period and a cast period. During the waiting period, all characters involved in the battle move slowly to the cast period, and once they reach that point, you'll be able to select your moves. During this period, though, if either character hits another character that's also in the cast period, you can ""interrupt"" their move, sending them a little bit farther back into the waiting period. It's a system that takes getting used to at first, but it doesn't take long to strategize around it.Overall, the hype behind this game was right on target; this game is one of the best RPGs that have come out for a long time. Although there's sadly no class system, there are plenty of skills to learn through the skill tree, and the amount of grinding that you end up doing doesn't feel too monotonous, as you'll quickly level up and earn extra rewards. Also, characters in your party level up at about the same time, so for those who just like to stick to a few characters, there's no need to worry that any other characters are falling behind."
,Recommended,256290,10000163,"Posted: 2 May, 2014",all,Jas i'm dyslexic,"if your plannig to get this game, BUY IT! it's got Wonderful art! plus a beautiful fairy tale story line! a great gift for all ages!"
