76561198055854369,Recommended,256290,10813113,"Posted: 25 June, 2014",all,BigBearDoinThangs,"I can say without a doubt Child of Light has been one of the biggest suprisies of the year for me. Being a fan of old-school JRPG's, I picked this game up the day it was released. I fell in love with the music and water-color art-style. I would even go so far as to recommend purchasing the OST, as this game contains some of the best pieces I've had the pleasure of listening to.The characters feel hand-crafted to the world. CoL manages to maintain a certain amount of cuteness without going over-board. Everyone in the world of Lemuria speaks in the a/b/a/b rhyming scheme, (common in children's books) which I adore. There isn't any voice acting aside from the narrator, but I don't feel that it detracts any from the game.My one complaint would be with the story at the beginning, as it was a bit hard to follow. The map is also a bit odd to use, but most of the time you won't even see it.Youwillhave to install Uplay in order to play CoL, which at first I was wary of. However, there are rewards obtainable from Uplay by completing achievements such as in-game items and background art which make it worthwhile.If you are looking for an RPG with an inspiring soundtrack, beautiful graphics, and a compelling story fit for all ages, be sure to give Child of Light a try."
