76561198077426450,Recommended,256290,10387559,"Posted: 7 June, 2014",all,Daxxramas85,"Child of Light is a great story with BEAUTIFUL graphics and artwork!There ..... i just summed it up in one sentence ..... but if that wasn't enough to convince you, I'll go ahead and go into a little more detail.Story: As i said it's an awesome story.  You play as a ""princess"" who has been poisoned and wakes up in another world.  You're main gold is to return to YOUR world to save your father who has become deathly ill with grief over your ""death"".  One thing that is very different but i thought was nice was that all the dialogue between the characters and the narrator were done in poem/balad type format.  So yes, it all rhymed lol.  I suppose you could say it added to the ""Immersion"" factor in the sense that people don't really TALK like that anymore.Graphics: Lovely hand-drawn backgrounds and characters.Gameplay: Child of Light is built upon the framework of a classic turn-based RPG, but also uses the often seen ""Move bar"", making combat slightly more dynamic and interactive than just ""pick move, use move"".  Using your little firefly elemental you can slow down enemies to make your moves go first or fall in just the right place on the move bar to be most effective.The skill trees for all the characters are EXPANSIVE but simplistic at the same time.  You can look ahead and see where you are going so you can plan out exactly what you want the character to do for your group, whether more damage focused or control or healing.  Each character (and there are several you will unlock during your journey) has primarily 3 skill trees that expand after you recover the moon in the game.  Most skills cost only one skill point which you get each time you gain a level and once you get the expansion some of the advance skills cost 2 points.  You gain levels fairly quickly and even if you don't use a character in battle it still levels up with the whole party.  I finished with most of my characters being low to high 40s.After the initial ""tutorial"" area, and you unlock your flight ability, navigating the world becomes a breeze.  The controls to fly and control that flight are simple and intuitive.  You really get the sense of freedom as you explore every nook and cranny for hidden secrets and chests.I think I've said enough.  If i haven't convinced you to give this game a play by now then nothing more i say is going to make a difference.This game is HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!!!Happy Gaming Guys..."
