76561198046276004,Recommended,256290,10003553,"Posted: 2 May, 2014",all,WulfgarVikingThunder,"CoL is innocative and interesting. In a genre that has some puzzle solving one would normally see real time combat CoL chooses to use an interesting twist on turn based RPG combat. There are still stats that decided damage, weakness, and resistance like one would assume, but there is also manipulation of attack order and the ability to time attacks correctly to interrupt an enemy attack.The art is inspiring and colorful, and the characters are unique and compelling. There is enough action between the dialouge that is doesn't feel heavy, but there is enough dialouge to guide an interesting story that fits the genre of bed time fairy tales. ""A little girl chosen as a child of light to fight a queen of darkness and reclaim a lost land"", that sort of thing.As for UPlay its not a perfect system, its annoying to have to run there program in addition to steam, in addition to the game itself, but I hadn't used my account with them since playing Far Cry 3 on PS3 about two years ago, and I had no trouble recovering my account and playing the game.Great game, reasonable price, you won't be disappointed with this addition to your steam library."
