76561198101685358,Recommended,256290,10455792,"Posted: 12 June, 2014",all,Gloomy Spirits,"Never would I have thought that steam could tell bedtime stories. If nothing else, the visuals are enough to take your breath away. the watercolor painting inspired artwork and fanatstical setting really sets the fairytale spirit of the game. However, you cant make a god narritive with pretty visuals alone, there has to be a gripping story and well one telling of it. The story is reminiscent of the classic fairy tale stories we heard as kids; it has a princess, a witch, magic, strange creatures, and a hero. Luckily it has enough original ideas to be far from cliche. The gameplay is very well done too. It's combat system is second to none and the puzzles will keep your brain working throughout the game without feeling like its just solvig the same simple puzzle over and over.  For the icing on the cake, we have the music. Written by Candian artist, Coeur de Pirate, it really sets the mood of the game. the dreamy piano gives it that bedtime story feeling, and the orchestral parts really emphasize the fantastic landscape and intense battle. If I could just sum this up, I would say it's a simple and intelligent game."
