76561198057129523,Recommended,256290,20206922,"Posted: 1 January, 2016",all,adzl33t,"I'm not the biggest fan of turn based game, but this is one of most engaging complulsive games I played (like playing at 3 AM gaming)There are two mechanics here that's makes way more entertaining than any Final Fantasy GameA loading bar interface that helps the player to find out who's turn is it, with a small window for any moves, when the player moves timed just right that can push their opponents back another turn (but can happen to the player too)and the firefly companion during waiting time can either provides health for player's character or slow down oppponents, this would give something the player to do why waiting for their turn, and give an extra sense of strategy to the game.Along with the ease to use in game system, there's also a crafting system that has it products to be use interchangable for the player's party, and simple skill trees. This is an easy to use RPG game that's great for first timers, yet allows veterans to think more deepy with the game in order to curb stomp opponents.As I'm writing this I only played easy mode, and only got 2-4 party members knocked out while hardly using my items, but there was plently of game, about over 17 hours of my first playthrough.The story is engaging with his melachony atmosphere and sense of humor, fun characters, and a simple coming of age story that use many typical perhaps some Grimm Tale tropes and archtypes, it may seem cliche, but the presentation of elegant art style made me interested playing though, direct and simple not bloated and overly complicated, but beautifully bittersweet.This is perhaps my favorite RPG game period, but keep in mind I'm not the biggest RPG fan.So for newcomers or experts, I think this would most likely interested them."
,Recommended,256290,17447368,"Posted: 8 August, 2015",all,Crazyi,"Overall - 8/10 I really enjoyed this game as a turn based RPG fan. I didn't score it higher because outside of the combat it doesn't really push the boundry, but its a fantastic itteration on the tradional.Story: Its like a poetic child's book. Not going to blow you away but its nice.Combat: Fantastic if you like turn based RPGs. I cannot explain this in a small paragraph, but basically your mouse has special powers and you can interupt enemy actions by timing things properly with character actions. Very fun take on the tradional format.Exploring - Little nooks to find, traps to dodge, and small little puzzles are fun but nothing new.Art Style - Certainly not next level but I really liked the visuals of the game. It adds to the story book feeling."
,Recommended,256290,10045709,"Posted: 7 May, 2014",all,LeapMaster,"Simply a beautiful, heartfelt game. The fairy-tale style takes a little getting used to, but the game is really just amazingly well polished and a great experience. The soundtrack is nothing short of amazing, the hand-drawn graphics are gorgeous, the characters somehow manage to feel un-tropey despite a few cliche characteristics, the worlds are a blast to explore, combat is simple yet surprisingly tactical, deep, and incredibly rewarding, and the story is a small rollercoaster ride from start to finish, even if it largely serves to simply tie everything together. I can't bring myself to name a single issue I had with the game, other than the always-in-iambic-pentamiter dialogue feeling a tad bit forced at a few points.All of the charm of a small indie title, with the talent and production of a large studio; definitely worth checking out. This game is one hell of an adventure."
