,Recommended,256290,9986042,"Posted: 30 April, 2014",all,Pleiades,"The game is undeniably beautiful, with the excellent score as accompaniment. The story is rhymed and whimsical to match, an ease and joy to read. The backgrounds are lovingly detailed, and the eagle-eyed would easily spot hidden treasures scattered across the land of Lemuria, and exploration is encouraged in side quests, opening up new sections of an area. The combat system may take some time to get used to, with certain elements of timing and luck required to get your skills or interrupts off, and learning it would make battles a breeze.While on the whole I would recommend this game, thus far there is a certain linearity; I had wandered ahead before returning to complete a quest, and later triggered a new story cutscene in a place I had already been to. The 2-member party size might seem very limiting as well, one assumes to encourage more active swapping.Edit on game completion: The replayability would come from collecting all the items, unlocking the skills, but if you're not one to do that, then leaving this game for a sale would be alright. One thing I should warn is that there is no brief break betwen the second last and the last boss, and I got a nasty shock from the transition. I myself would like to read all the dialogue all over again, but this is subjective."
