,Recommended,256290,9983680,"Posted: 30 April, 2014",all,GECK,"It's truly abeautifulpiece.A few words on the aesthetics:The artstyle has a nice oil painting feel to it which is pleasing to the eyes.The soundtrack is really melancholic invoking true empathy for the characters as well as helping the immersion significantly.The dialogue is very poetic and is not afraid to plunge into the olden English which gives the whole story a classical fairytail story feeling to it.A few thoughts on gameplay:While the combat system is the game's main mechanic, I don't believe that it is the true focus of the game.I believe that the game's main focus is exploration and discovery, to explore this new and unfamiliar world, to find hidden nooks and crannies filled with treasure chests and lore.However the game can be played in both ways:If you prefer the RPG elements and combat over exploration lore and discovery, I'd recommend setting the difficulty to HARD so combat plays a more deeper role in the game and you'll need to focus more on gaining levels as you progress.If you prefer to explore this 2D open world, looking for treasure chests, exploring seemingly abandoned houses and whatnot, I'd recommend setting the difficulty to NORMAL for maximum pleasure, this way dealing with the occasional monsters along the way as you continue to explore should be sufficient for you to advance through the game in an enjoyable pace."
