,Not Recommended,256290,33890209,Posted: 29 July,all,Razomir,"At first this game seemed like it was right up my alley. But perhaps that was my mistake because I expected more. A LOT more. The game tries to be a story-driven stylized gem but fails in pretty much every aspect. The graphics are in fact in a unique style but that style looks lazy and very soon the marionette physics get tiresome. The combat is both simplistic and shallow - it is not so much turn based as cooldown based. To be fair the Igniculus assistance has some clever uses but I feel like so much more could have been done with it. The story is generic - [spoilers]young princess unites quarreling tribes, beats the evil queen and retakes her rightful crown[/spoilers]. Unskippable cutscenes are inexcusable. Worst still is the attempt to make all dialogue rhyme, often resulting in nonsensical chatter - perfect example of a great idea executed horribly wrong.It just leaves you unsatisfied. Like a great looknig meal which turns out to have no seasoning so it tastes bland. I DO strongly recommend it if you are 7 and want to waste some time, but in general it is just a bedtime story, and not a very good one at that."
