,Recommended,256290,16983444,"Posted: 10 July, 2015",all,report ancient for feed,"After just having finishedChild of Light, I think I can safely say that this is now one of my all-time favorite games. At a glance, you can already tell that the game looks absolutely beautiful and sports a soundtrack to match, while making sure that neither element compromises the substance of gameplay. The utilization of a timeline of events rather than a traditional turn-based combat system makes sure the game stays interesting well past the end of the story, which is rather well-paced without overstaying its welcome or forcing you to backtrack.In terms of downsides, this game does not officially support laptop graphics cards, so if you're not sure how the game will perform I would recommend playing the demo before purchasing. Uplay is a major downside according to most people, but I have personally never had a problem with the service. Another common complaint is that the rhyming script feels forced at times, a statement which I am forced to agree with (but I must note that it rarely affected my enjoyment of the game).There isn't much to hate in this game; overall, it's very solid and enjoyable. If you're evenremotelyinterested in turn-based RPGs, I very strongly recommend this game for you."
