,Recommended,256290,18870893,"Posted: 4 November, 2015",all,DreamStar,"Gorgeous game with a sweet story told fully in poetry ryhmes.The game looks like a storybook come to life, which is appropriate for the story being told. My only complaint graphically is that the main character Aurora look more like a 3d model than the rest of the cast and enemies, which looks more 2d... so she often seems out of place sometimes.The music is simple and sweet, but can be repetitive.The gameplay like a mash up of a bunch of different style old school RPGS, giving you turn-based action choices along with the real-time battle action bar to stir things up. You can swap out characters mid battle to utilize everyone's unique skills and each caharacter can be customized to an extent by choosing which path to follow when leveling up on the character's skill tree. Learning enemies strengths and weakness make all the difference in this game and if you are used to games where this is the key to success, the battles can get repetitive towards the end of the game.I enjoyed fully exploring the areas, searching for the hidden items and completing side quests. I was able to pretty much clear everything on the first run through. As a result, once you beat the game there isn't much replay value. But this game was enjoyable enough the first time around to be worth the purchase price.And Side Note: UPLAY is required to run the game, which I had to sign up an account to do. I didn't like that too much, because I read that a lot of other people had crash troubles with this game because of it... but luckily I didn't."
