76561198116083694,Recommended,256290,10044554,"Posted: 7 May, 2014",all,春日咲子,Holy♥♥♥♥♥♥ the game is beautiful and addicting.  Just wish I had a little more time to play it.
,Recommended,256290,10003693,"Posted: 2 May, 2014",all,fictitiouspresence,"This entire game is written in rhyming verse. That, along with the instantly distinctive hand-drawn art style and beautiful instrumental music combine to form one of the most stylish RPG's to be released in recent memory. The presentation is nothing short of masterful, and if you enjoy the artistic expression inherent in games, you'll need no further reason to go play this right now.This is a turn-based RPG, with an excellent and well-balanced combat system reminiscent of the Grandia series, with all attacks requiring charge time and being interruptable. That, mixed with the ability to hot-swap party members and influence the timing of actions with your firefly familiar leads to a system that's surprisingly deep. It's easy to miss just how well-designed the combat is, but notice how: 1) you can't always just spam your best attack -- you have to watch what can interrupt you, 2) you don't always just focus fire on one enemy, since you might want to prioritize interrupting their attacks, 3) the defend command is critically useful, and 4) you actually need to use your party swap mechanism for the tougher fights. It's really rare for a system to pull that off!I played on Hard mode and found the challenge level to be perfect (so I imagine RPG veterans would find ""Normal"" far too easy); I struggled to survive and used copious amounts of potions in several battles, but victory was always attainable with decent strategy. Unless you're revisiting an old area that you now overlevel, you can't just spam the basic attack and expect to win!When not playing a combat or enjoying the poetry-filled story, you'll be exploring the world in 2D platformer mode. At first, it feels like it might be a full-on metroidvania, but you get the ability to fly and open all the locked paths very early in the game, so it's really more of a straightforward 2d action segment. There's some very light puzzle solving, a handfull of side quests, and plenty of hidden things to collect -- but it's generally more of a relaxing walk through the scenery.As for drawbacks? There really aren't any, aside from Uplay and Ubisoft's utterly perplexing day-0 DLC (why would you buy in-game items? They're not even particularly *good* items and you can get them easily by playing.) I could ask for more -- more levels, more skill variety, perhaps better level design with harder puzzles ... but there could always be more stuff in a game. What's here constitutes a solid experience that I can heartily recommend to anyone who enjoys turn-based RPG's and the fairytale aesthetic.Overall: 5/5 -- My favorite game so far this year."
76561198038397525,Recommended,256290,10004237,"Posted: 3 May, 2014",all,CRUEL42,"Child of Light is such a visual treat,with some decent rpg mechanics.It won't take a very long time to beat,Nor very many hardcore gamer tricks.The style is like a children's fairy tale,In a colored, wondrous fantasy realm,But if these rhymes cause your brain to derail,Then this game will most surely overwhelm.The gameplay divided into two parts:Exploration and combat; no surprise.It is rather simple as the game starts,And further, intoduces complex size.Exploration gives very free movement,In a lovely and detailed 2-d plane.There are simple puzzles to circumvent,And many small, hidden items to gain.There is no currency or trade system,No massive inventory to manage.Among the types you collect is the gem,Which you equip to give a combat edge.The combat is mostly a turn based fare,Characters all wait to cast an action.There is a real time aspect; be aware,Though keeping it up is a distraction.The skill trees are kinda boring and dull,with no real complexity to see.Branches don't feel rewarding when all full,Character building is rather easy.The story is a fanciful journey,of a young girl who had just lost her way.She must explore an unknown world and see,If her light can keep the darkness at bay.The mood is quite somber; the theme, mature,Despite the shiny, lighthearted facade.Like folk stories of olden days that stir,Some unease with its lessons to be made.If I had to: 8.5 out of 10,I look forward to playing it again."
