76561198091662675,Recommended,256290,16951796,"Posted: 8 July, 2015",all,brenden208,"This was one of the most amazing games that I have ever played, and I would definitely reccomend it to anyone who is a fan of this genre. **Note: I have seen some other reviews mentioning a save glitch that deletes their progress, and I too experienced this glitch; I will put my solution to this problem below the rest of the review so you do not have to lose hours of gameplay as I did.*The game has wonderful pacing, with a slow acceleration, to where it never really feels slow, or boring*The story is quite charming, and told in a way which makes it ever better: I doubt I will ever forget the plight of the Child of Light*The world is absolutely beautiful, with a hand-painted aesthetic, and wonderful characters*The soundtrack is enchanting, and complements the story immensely, not to mention being more than good enough to stand alone*So much more that cannot be put into wordsThe only problem I have with this game is that it requires Uplay to run, and I probably lost a good 8+ hours to a save glitch (solution below). But overall, the game itself is fantastic, and I give it a 10/10.**To solve the save glitch problem (which seems to be caused by Uplay failing to save your progress to the cloud, and then when it next starts up, and does its routine save synchronization, prioritizing the cloud over your local files, thus deleting the progress it failed to save), I ended up going into Uplay's settings (the gear in the upper right hand corner), and under General, I unchecked 'Enable cloud save synchronization...', and as well, under Network, I checked 'Always start Uplay in offline mode.' Then, as an extra fail-safe, I used task manager to end all of Uplay's processes (GameLauncher, Uplay.exe, and WebCore) after starting the game each time, effectively eliminating all chance of Uplay accessing the cloud, and deleting my local files. Additionally, I always waited for the auto-save symbol to completely fade before exiting the game, and always exited directly to Windows. These last two may be unnecessary, but I had already lost hours to the glitch, so I was taking no chances. This worked very well for me, and I hope it works for others."
