,Recommended,256290,18360335,"Posted: 6 October, 2015",all,bryanhbell,"Child Of Lightis my favorite among the games I've played so far in 2015 (which included some pretty good ones:Valiant Hearts,Broken Age,Never Alone,Mark Of The Ninja, andOri And The Blind Forest).Many well-executed elements combine to produce an immersive fairy tale atmosphere. Thebeautiful watercolor-style artworkreminds me ofArthur Rackham's illustrations. The music, by singer-songwriterCœur de pirate, is melodic and memorable.The narration, by actress Caroline Dhavernas (known recently for her role of Dr. Alana Bloom on the TV showHannibal) perfectly captures the sound of a mother telling a bedtime story. The story itself is well-developed, intricate, and moving.All of the narration and dialogue is told in rhyming poetry. I've read that some people say this style is off-putting or sounds forced. I enjoyed it and felt it enhanced the game experience immeasurably.The gameplay is a combination of light platformer and RPG. Periodic battle sequences are turn-based in a style that I've read is similar to the gamesGrandiaand theFinal Fantasyseries (I've played none of these). I'm not really fond of twitch gameplay, so I enjoyed this slower-paced battle system.When I finished the game, I was sad that it was over and wished I'd taken it more slowly to savor the experience."
