76561198010079743,Recommended,256290,16527571,"Posted: 19 June, 2015",all,SeaSaltSong,"A lot of complaints you will see are about uplay. yes you need uplay to play this game, however once you set it up it becomes a non-issue. Steam will launch uplay, sign you in, and launch the game all under about 10 seconds. Annoying? Sure. A reason not to play this wonderful game? not at all.This is a turn based JRPG-style game that is becoming more rare these days. The artwork is fantastic, and the music is hypnotising. All dialogue is in rhyme, which technically makes this story an epic. One long poem. All of it is so well put together it makes me think someone at Ubisoft overheard someone complain when people call a video game ""art"" and they accepted the challenge. Artwork is an understatement for this game.Combat is very fluid. There is a ""timeline"" at the bottom of the screen that keeps track of your characters and the enemies. You move through the timeline based on your speed stat, and any buffs/debuffs you have going. When you reach the end you hit the casting portion of the timeline. This is when you choose your action. you then move through this part of the timeline and complete the action at the end. Some actions are longer to complete than others. If you or an enemy takes damage while in the casting portion, before pulling the attack off, you are ""inturrupted"" and lose your turn basically. It's a great aspect that requires more strategy then ""pick big spell make big boom.""Overall it's a very enjoyable game, and New Game+ makes every game batter."
