76561198005768523,Recommended,256290,20548772,"Posted: 15 January, 2016",all,Biño,"This game is like a melancholic fairytale with a wonderful story and charm. A truly wonderful role-playing experience where the incredible artstyle and the fact that every dialogue is rhymed by the characters makes it really unique. Throw in a grandia styled battle system where you can strategically delay enemy actions by attacking while they're winding up an attack and where you can use a fairy to either heal your own party members or slow enemy actions down and you have some real strategic encounters.On the other hand the game can get a bit repetitive because of three things that add up:- The character customisation is pretty simple with a short list of spells/actions and equippable items.- The rhyming, while amazingly well thought out in most areas, can easily get on your nerves in others.- The soundtrack, while hauntingly beautiful, consists of very few tracks.Overall I absolutely enjoyed my time with this game and would really recommend it to anyone. It could be a great entry point for people new to the jrpg-genre and certainly was worth my time as well"
