76561198108171481,Recommended,256290,21187618,"Posted: 13 February, 2016",all,CarniverousPwny,"I usually don't write reviews, but with so many people having an issue with uPlay I thought I would post what worked for me.I read the reviews and comments before purchasing Child of Light on sale and I figured if I couldn't get it to work that it wouldn't be a total loss.So here's what worked for me:1. I did install the game, but DID NOT do the first time setup right away.2. Before first time set up, I went online to Uplay and downloaded it from their site. Then made an account.3. I then went to steam to get the game code. Copied it.4. Went back to Uplay and went to ""activate product""5. Pasted code and it was added to my library.6. THEN I finally hit play in Steam and did the first time set up. It asked me to link steam with Uplay. I did but I don't think you have to.And the game has run smoothly ever since :)I must say, I greatly enjoy this game and was glad I was able to get it working. The music and gameplay are calming and fun at the same time. I love the art design as well.I haven't finished the game yet, but I greatly look forward to it and I hope what worked for me will help others enjoy this game as well. It is too wonderful to give up on."
