76561198007205207,Recommended,256290,11456755,"Posted: 28 July, 2014",all,Parsifal,"Have you ever wondered what a team of creative and artistic geniuses like say those that Disney worked with during the Fantasia period may have done with a media like games? I don't say this carelessly, but Child of Light is as close an answer to that as I've seen in the more than three decades I've been playing games. Don't get me wrong, this is not the greatest game ever made per se, but it does succeed at making a game 'art' in a way where I don't think anyone else has ever succeeded. The story, the art design, the sound, the gameplay all come together in an experience that really exemplifies that this is something more than a run of the mill short game you've signed on for. The game itself is a very digestible package, probably clocking in at about 5-10 hours to complete both the story and then go back and tie off loose ends if you so choose.At $15 the price of admission is a little on the steep end but for the quality of the experience it's well worth every penny. I can happily recommend this game to most audiences, in particular those with younger children just becoming literate and ready to begin RPG games. Also, as the father of a young girl I appreciate seeing titles like this that provide a leed female role that for too long has been absent in gaming's balance.In short, BUY THIS GAME. :)"
