76561198127436536,Recommended,256290,12422157,"Posted: 9 October, 2014",all,Zedd,"Worth getting just for the art alone! The storyline is obviously a bit childish but the rhyming verse and the cool art managed to keep me interested. The combat system is a decent challenge so long as you set it to Expert. You can't just hold your finger on ""Attack"" and expect to win like in many turn-based games.My only gripe would be that you have to hold your finger down on the mouse a lot (to hinder enemies with your firefly ally) which is a killer if you have RSI."
,Recommended,256290,12427625,"Posted: 9 October, 2014",all,yampuff,"Refreshing, memorable and touching. In a time of dark, gritty, alpha-male heroes, the chance to be transported to a watercolored, fairytale world of fantastic creatures and beautiful princesses is one that could not be missed. I would have been satisfied will simply a beautiful, arty game - but Child of Light has so much more to offer.I honestly can not praise the art direction enough; 3D models such as Aurora herself blends seemlessly into the tradionally painted backgrounds. The world moves and breathes as you move, fog rising and falling, creatures tumbling about in the background and light filtering through branches. More than once I would just pause and stare at the detailed backdrops. All this accompanied by a wonderful musical  score.The question you might ask is; style over substance? It's not fair to blame other games for relying too heavily on graphics but giving this game a pass because it's 'pretty'. But while the style, music and atmosphere are very much an integral part of the game, it doesn't end there. Child of Light offers us memorable characters, an excellent RPG system, plenty of locations to explore, chests to unearth and open, bosses and minibosses to fight and a well-paced story to follow.For the first time in perhaps years I found myself in tears during a game, really caring about the characters and what happened to them. Yes, the poetic verse is occasionally stilted, but when it works, it truly works. Tristis in particular delivers some of the best-delivered, most harrowing lines of the game, as well as Aurora and Igniculus's little conversations.Is it a ground-breakng story, full of twists and unexpected endings? No, but then it doesn't have to be. The gameplay and character interaction were more than enough. In fact, the only complaint I really have with the game is it could have done with more locations to explore and more side quests. And when the only thing you want from a game is more, I think you have something good on your hands.I highly recommend Child of Light to anyone interested in an interesting, unique, thoughtful game. A game with a princess who has a sword and travels the forest barefoot - with a ragtag band of humorous characters."
,Recommended,256290,12429956,"Posted: 9 October, 2014",all,T-cat,"The art style of this RPG game is what drew me in and let me tell you,it delivers. This game is a gorgeous feast of beauty for the eyes! The player will explore several types of terrain inhabited by very different kinds of creatures, with the opportunity to participate in various sidequests. All speech/text is written in verse, which is both fun and humorous, and keeps your attention well. The controls are sparse and easy to learn. The combat is somewhat advanced and certain bosses require multitasking to defeat. By the end of the game, you'll feel like you've just been read a very good bed time story, or had a very good dream. I put about 13 hours into the game to complete it, and I feel that's just right.My only two gripes (which are rather small) are first that I feel there are too many (by one) playable characters in the game. Second, I couldn't figure out how to defend in order to avoid interruption during casting. Every time I defended and then casted only to be interrupted, a tutorial box would pop up and remind me that interruption can be avoided by defending. Pity it never worked for me but with a little patience, my progression was not hindered.If you're looking for a game that is beautiful to look at with simple controls and light content that doesn't require a large investment of time to finish, look no further than this game."
