,Recommended,256290,14285407,"Posted: 1 February, 2015",all,Fluxuation,"Very good game overall. The story was quite good and has some serious elements, which I didn't expect due to the whimsical art style and silly dialogue. The art style makes the game look beautiful, and makes the differences between light and dark even more obvious. The music is great, and the dialogue is humorous, though the constant rhyming starts to grate over time. The combat reminds me of the final fantasy series, with the addition of being able to interrupt. The interrupt can be both a blessing and a curse. It's great because it opens up different strategies, but a couple of times I ran into the problem where the enemies were so fast and split up just enough that I couldn't do anything but defend for quite a few turns. However, late game this system can be extremely exploited (the final boss didn't even get a chance to attack me). On the subject of battling and difficulty, I would recommend that if you want any kind of challenge you choose the highest difficulty, otherwise there is very little challenge."
