76561198031190688,Recommended,256290,30915642,Posted: 2 April,all,CompletelyNormalGuy,"There are a lot of things going on with this game, so I guess I'll just break it into parts. I'll start with the gameplay:This game has a two-dimensional overworld. Enemies are shown on the overworld, and can be engaged or avoided. Combat takes place in a separate battle screen. From a gameplay perspective, the combat system is probably the most interesting and novel thing about the game. There are a number of options for slowing enemies down, and striking a foe at the right time can ""interrupt"" them. Of course they can also interrupt you if you aren't careful. This can often make combat feel like you are juggling enemies, which I liked.On to story and writing: The story is very much a straight-up fairy tale about a princess coming of age and saving her kingdom. The characters are fairly colorful and varied. Also, all dialogue is written in rhyme, which could be a positive or a negative. I personally found it endearing, but I can see how others could find it maddening. Overall, it's a fairly light-hearted adventure.I liked the visuals too. They were fairly simple, and high-contrast, which I thought worked well with the story."
