,Recommended,256290,13206299,"Posted: 2 December, 2014",all,Torres,"Child of Light is a warm dreamlike, sugar coated, fuzzy and light game about a princess that does stuff. You'll get no spoilers from me. The game is easy to play, easy to pick up, easy to get into, and a joy to explore. As I am writing this I haven't finished the game. But I wanted to write it since it is on sale and maybe many of you are on the fence about it.GraphicsLike a warm fire on a cold winter day. This game shows you a world where its ok to lean back a little and smile. The use of color and the smoothness of the animation, gameplay, short cutscenes and overall world are fantastic. Everything looks like a childrens book. And that is a fun and happy place to be.GameplayIt feels like there are almost two games here. In one you lazily float around in the world and collect items. You get to see all the cute buildings in the sky and solve increasingly difficult puzzles. And in the other game you have a turn based rpg. Where you can costumize your team of characters (via skill trees) and have an influence on their equipment. The combat is fast paced and fun. There is room in it to improve and really become quite good at it. Overall the gameplay is enjoyable and there really is more game than you think there is at first glance.SoundThey have done a great job on the sound. It compliments the graphics of the game. The narrator is smooth and not obtrusive. The rhyming way the story is told really does make you feel like youre in a childrens book and further engages you in the world. Music is clean and light, I haven't tired of it and I don't think I will.StoryIt is at its core a childrens tale. The story is simple and well done. You won't be blown away by it, but expect to be charmed by it. Like just the right amount of cookies before you get sick.Overall Score 8/10.I think the only thing that kept me from giving it a higher score is that in terms of scale it isn't as big as some of the other games. I don't think it is up to par with the heavy hitters like Bioshock and Fallout. But for the price I honestly considered giving it 10/10. For this to be on sale as low as it is, is a bargain. You are getting hours and hours of gameplay. The combat will want to make you try out different things. The characters are likable, the world is sweet and dreamlike, the music is beautiful without feeling overbearing, and the story is charming. Get it, eveyone should own this game."
