76561198086505175,Recommended,256290,13399821,"Posted: 16 December, 2014",all,[POEX]An-Tarxamon,"My rating for Child of Light: 100/100This game deserves it.  It shows a fairy tale. rich story, which changes dramatically and show us, that sometimes we have to grow to gain, what we want. Artistic impressions are beyond most games limits.""Child. Tuck yourself in bedAnd let me tell a storyOf Lemuria, a long lost kingdom,And a girl born for glory.""Story is rich and contains a lot of details, that give the chance to think about it. Despair, aspiration, resolution, fights and even love, are present during each moment of the game. All is situated as a fairy tale, but it is not only pretty and cheerful, but many times, it goes right under the skin and draws into the storyline, desinged as a poetry, there is even a storyteller here!Characters surprise in variety, their progress can also be seen during playthrough. Leading by firstly hesitating, then decisive Aurora, against forces of Queen of Night. Their changes are sometimes shocking, loyals are betrayed, exiled forgiven, sad became joyful, love fulfilled. There can by seen inspirations even from mythologies, like Cuchulain (celtic, here Kategida leader). Also, they interact within the party, revealing another deep ideas and findings. Mystic presence of Queen of Light linked with Aurora's dad's fate are completing this mosaic. Not forgetting the shiny, cheerful firefly, called Igniculus.Visual is beyond my expectations. Style looks like painted with watercolors, animations are precise, all looks soft and filled with magic. Backgrounds show variety and are meaningful for actual game moment.Soundtrack is also a masterpiece. Under the active supervision of Coeur de Pirate, we have here a composition of piano, violin, flute and other instruments, that help to enhance the atmosphere.  If you are eager to, there is a chance to buy it on Coeur's bandcamp for a reasonable price.Battles are designed in old-style RPG's as turns, combined with real-time element. This gives an opportunity to interact and make strategic moves to turn odds in your favor. But beware, some creatures are better not to be interrupted, which leads me to point, that also there is a chance of counterattack, what makes fights even more interesting.This brings me also to multiplayer. Second player can control Igniculus and be helpful taking unreachable chests and during fights slowing enemies and healing our characters. Roles are different for each player, which gives accent on teamwork. Believe me, everything is much easier then.There are some negatives, but they are not directly linked to the game, that is why I mention them here separately and do not affect my rating.Firstly, you have to have uPlay installed, which can be annoying, on the other side, completing the achievements gives you points to receive refinements for this and another uPlay linked games.Secondly, your CPU have to support microarchitecture SSE4, SSE4a for AMDs. So, do not be shocked, if your speed is sufficient, but text message will state, that is outdated. This is not mentioned in minimum requirements, but that is mistake for Ubisoft and Ubisoft Montréal, not game alone.I would also be glad to purchade the soundtrack with the game as some form of bundle, but this is just my desire, what was already fulfilled in another way (via bandcamp).To sum it up, if you are fun of high quality RPGs, fairy tales, rich stories, crystallis music, poetry, you do not have to look as many games to fill all your requirements. There is one, Child of Light, which joins them all.Aurora: ""Locked""Igniculus: ""I am not shocked.""Breathtaking. Highly recommended."
