,Recommended,256290,30380332,Posted: 7 March,all,waelhadaya,"First of all, I think this is a must have for any Turn-Based RPG fan, almost everything about it is perfect, it’s simply very charming.The artwork, the atmosphere, the characters, the gameplay mechanics, the music, they are amazing, especially the music it’s so beautiful and emotional it makes a great memory for me, although I wish there were more tracks, sometimes they tend to repeat a little bit.I enjoyed the combat system so much, I stand to be corrected but I think it’s one of kind, I mean the way it handles the turn is so immersive, the way you can gain advantage and disadvantages based on the way you attack enemies (normal, getting ambushed, or surprise attack) is unique as well, the way you collect wishes to replenish HP and MP is nice and fun too.The way the story was written is again so beautiful, the way the text rhymes is one of a kind and I disagree with people thinking that it gets old, actually it’s so well written and perfectly woven from start to end, kudos to the developers for such an artistic touch.I lost count of all the thing this game does perfectly, but there are a very few minor cons as well even though they didn’t affect my experience at all, for example most of the potions you collect are useless, you have them as spells, also why can’t I use three protagonist instead of two? It feels like this game was designed for three anyway, also the leveling tree felt a bit messy sometimes, and I can’t help but to notice a balancing problem, and without spoiling anything, the way you can abuse the paralyze system end game makes the game too easy as you can literally freeze your enemies the whole game and win flawlessly.All in all this is a great game, a must have in my opinion even full price, I finished this game in 24 hours, but half of that time was just grinding to level up (I love doing that in RPG’s), it felt hard to say goodbye to this one after finishing it, I give this game an excellent 9 out of 10."
