,Recommended,256290,26673784,"Posted: 18 November, 2016",all,Alierris But Spoopy,"While by no means the best game I've ever had the pleasure of playing, on a personal level this is my favorite game of all time.Pro'sEven though it's a really solid RPG, like 8/10, the real pull of this game is it's exceptional art style and good characters and story. The combat uses a really fun system, where by hitting an enemy with a skill or attack while there casting you can bump them back on the timeline, effectivey making them miss a turn, but beware, they can also do this to you which adds layers of depth to the game. The game uses the same engin as Rayman Legends, making the game breathtakingly beautiful. The orchestral soundtrack is also briliant, sounding wonderfully melancholy.ConsThe two small problems I have is that the system involving Oculi can be a little clunky at times, making equipping and removing them get a little tedious at times. On top of that the skill tree system, while I like the customization for every character it gives you, is rather cluttered, making it hard to have each character be exactly what you want them to be.Child of Light is a briliant game, amd it's few flaws are more than made up for by the great gameplay and exeptional presentation. All in all, an easy 8.5 out of 10."
