,Recommended,256290,21613941,"Posted: 3 March, 2016",all,Dicetower,"(Unless this is your first RPG, you're going to want to play on Expert mode and consider increasing the battle speed.)Child of Light is a beautiful game. Its overworld is like a giant, living painting.Exploring plays a bit like a platformer (though you are given a lot of freedom in how you move around), and battles are triggered by touching enemies. There are countless secrets littered all over the map.The battles are turn-based and use an interruption mechanic. Being attacked while casting your attack/item/spell delays your turn. You can utilize this to disadvantage enemies, sometimes forcing them to take numerous hits in a row. Very satisfying.The biggest flaws are the low difficulty, and writing. Expert mode feels like Normal mode in other games. You'll solve the few puzzles in seconds. Challenging enough to be fun, but a higher difficulty mode would have been great.The entire game is written in rhyme which gets old very fast. It holds back the character interactions, and I think the game could have been much better without the gimmick.That said, Child of Light is a fantastic game and I think it's well worth its price."
