76561198034629887,Recommended,256290,16914600,"Posted: 6 July, 2015",all,demonflowers,"I really loved this game.  The art and sound design are amazing.  The whole game is styled like a children's storybook and it works really well.  But not only is it beautiful (seriously this is one of the best looking games I've ever played), it is really well made.  The level design is amazing and the battle system is really good.  I actually dismissed the battle system at first, thinking it was just super simplistic turn based game play, but there is actually a lot of depth and complexity.  Being able to manipulate the turn order was really important, very fun and required a lot of skill.I do have a few little quibbles.  First of all, the rhymes.  While it is a cute idea, I found a distressing number of the rhymes to be kind of weak.  Thankfully most of the game isn't voice acted (there is a narrator occasionally, but that's it), so you can sort of ignore this.I also didn't like the fact that you can only use two characters at once during combat.  You can get eight playable characters (nine with downloadable content) with a really diverse set of skills and limiting us to only using two at once is sort of frustrating and basically meant I never used most of the characters except occasionally in boss fights.  This is especially perplexing as there can be three enemies on the field at once.That being said, this is still an amazing game.  Although obviously it is not a game for everyone.  Are you a gamer that needs everything grim and dark and shooty?  This is not the game for you.  But if you can get in touch with your inner child (or inner fairy princess) then you should really get this game."
