76561198207445511,Recommended,256290,25285359,"Posted: 1 September, 2016",all,mypattytoo,"This is one of the most charming and engaging games I've played in a long time. You explore the world in a sidescrolling platform style, but with some mechanics that are pretty unique to this story. (For example, you can control both the main character and a mote of light as well. Both have abilities and unique ways of interacting with the environment.)There are simple environmental puzzles, which makes it interesting without being particularly over challenging.When you interact with villains, the action becomes very Japanese roleplay game turn based play but with an emphasis on timing and a few other twists. I felt like I was engaging with something new, rather than simply playing in a certain known style due to these alterations. It was great!You can collect characters for your team, explore the environment, fly, and influence character builds in meaningful ways with interesting skill trees and add on items.The storyline is like a child's fairy tale, with all the innocent sing song quality and the underlying heavy themes.I found the play to be pretty stress relieving, as I could take time in combat to really think through what I wanted to do. I could also go back to earlier areas and just explore with low level foes for a bit, if I wanted to game without thinking much about it. After you finish the game, that is also an option. You can go back and revisit and explore areas, just for the joy of doing it.Visually, the game is just beyond stunning and the attention to detail (like the cursor being able to make the character's hair swish about in different ways) were suprising and charming.The only criticism I have of the game is the somewhat abrupt and rushed feel to the end. I would have appreciated a bit smoother transition.All in all, one of my favorite games in recent years.Gorgeous. Sweet. Entertaining."
