,Recommended,256290,20238802,"Posted: 2 January, 2016",all,Del Mingus,"tl:dr version:- an enjoyable and beautiful looking game that combines metroidvania style levels with jrpg style combat though it start to feel dull and repetitive towards the end.Full version:This game sees you play as Aurora, a young Austrian princess who wakes up in a strange land called Lemuria and must try and find a way to get back to her father with the help of some friends who join her along the way. The gameplay is interesting as it combines metroidvania style levels with jrpg style combat and its actually a good combination. It also has a greats setting in Lemuria and is a visually beautiful game.Good points:- the game looks beautiful and the animation is like something from a fairytale book which fits the game really well. Lemuria makes for a great setting as well with its strange and varied inhabitants and locations- i quite liked the combat in this game. You can see enemies moving around the levels and bumping into them initiates combat. A type of active battle system with a progress bar is used, where the key is to interrupt your enemies attack during the casting phase or avoiding having your attacks being interrupted.  On top of this a firefly you control can be hovered over an enemy to slow theirprogress to their next attack, hover over allies to heal them as well as picking up hp and mp boosts. This lends a tactical approach to battles-the soundtrack for this game is quite nice and really adds to the games atmosphereBad points:- the games story is a bit dull which is a shame. The characters all speak in rhyming lines which kind of limits story development and gets annoying after a while. Given Lemuria seems like an interesting place it feels like a missed oppurtunity to not have an interesting story to go with it.- the game does start to get a bit repetitive towards the end. There is a new game + mode but after playing the game once i didnt feel like i wanted to go through it again."
