76561198121478013,Recommended,256290,16435501,"Posted: 15 June, 2015",all,Zombie Chinchilla,"I don't often review games, but I felt like I should for this.First off, this game is great. Very JRPG-esque, with timed battles and leveling up. It plays through wonderfully, though, where you can slow your opponents down and give yourself health while waiting for it to be your turn in battle. The battles are fun, especially since I'm not often a fan of this style. It's also nice that you see the enemies and can avoid engaging in battle. You can even shine a light on them to make them cower so that you can pass by without engaging.The setting and art is fantastic. Probably my favorite of any video game, not even kidding. Every part of it is gorgeous.Finally: Uplay. Yes, it's frustrating DRM. But it's not a reason to pass this game by. Just put in your email and password, check that you don't want any updates from them, and that's all. The fact that people are not recommending this game because of the Uplay is cheap and dishonest, honestly."
