,Recommended,256290,16439837,"Posted: 16 June, 2015",all,Blackhawk Aya,"A game with a fantastic and whimsical start full of fantasy and promise ends up pittering out in the end with a rushed ending and a lack of what it held so strongly in the beginning.I loved the start of this game. It had me entranced so fully and I was sucked into it at once. The music is lovely and the art is something special. The drawn world with the 3d girl. It's beyond lovely. It's beautiful. The fairy tale like beginning of a little girl who is in this magical world. I was truly in love.The game play is clean with its little faults here and there and the combat is simple. There is room for thought and cleverness when you fight  or you can just push your way through every battle.About half way through I feel the game starts to lose a lot of it's charm. A little after you meet Aurua's sister is where I feel the magic starts to fade away. The story teller speaks to you for the last time till the end of the game and it's where you lose your sister as a party member that the magic just seems to fade away. And by the end it's just gone.It's a rushed ending with a final boss just thrown at you with no build up. It just happens. And it ends about as fast as that. Your little child of light spends half the game not being a child and certainly doesn't end being a child. The issue with her father feels empty and forgotten. And Umbra, your big bad, feels uneventfull and not really that much of an issue.Understandably this is not a big game and there is only room for what there is room for. But I feel, despite that, the ending shouldn't have been what it was. The story, to me, is just as important as everything else and when you fall so terribly short it's disappointing though I do not regret any money or time spent on the game. It was pretty and good for what it was, even with the lack luster ending.It's said this game is boring, though I can see how one might feel that way, I do not find it so. It's a typical rpg with talking. You walk some your characters stop and talk. You fight a couple battles your characters stop and talk. That's just familiar ground to me. The story itself is simple, perhaps boring? I found it enchanting. I suppose if you like whimsical and fanciful fairy tale like stories this would be a game for you, otherwise, perhaps not. For all it's faults and troublesome little issues it's a pretty game with a strong story start and a faltering end. Worth a single  playthrough and the few dollars it costs when it is on sale."
