,Recommended,256290,13731956,"Posted: 30 December, 2014",all,Tiggz,"Oh My God.I haven't even beat this game yet and it's one of the best games I've ever had the chance of playing. Bought it for 5.99 during the Winter Sale and can honestly say, one of the best purchases I've ever made.Seriously. Read on for more.Gameplay wise, you can fly around and do pretty much everything. It kind of reminds  me of Dust -An Elysian Tail in how the map works, but combat is turn based instead of hack and slash. Speaking of gameplay-  i LOVE LOVE LOVE LOVE how the characters interact with each other! Everyone speaks in a rhyming meter and its PERFECT for the type of game they were going for! The story is rich and the characters are amazing.Speaking of the combat system - it's something I havent seen in a while. Basically you have a ""Wait"" period, then a ""cast"" period. If you get hit while you're casting an attack, then you get interrupted and set back on the wait period. It's really quite interesting - you have to time your attacks properly so that you can intterupt your enemies.You get loads of party members (as I'm writing this, I have had a total of 5 different members, excluding Aurora). You can only have one person helping you per battle, but you can switch them out mid battle without any penalty. Every party member is slightly different - you have a healer/jester character, a mage, an archer, a swordsman, and a tank (as far as I've seen). I will update this further if I get more party members. You also get a firefly, Igniculus, who talks to you and gives you advice, as well as being usable to light up dark passages and interact with puzzles throughout the world map. In addition he is crucial for battles, where you can shine light on your enemies and slow their speed in a battle, which is crucial to winning.The augment system with the Oculi crystals is pretty simple to get the hang of. It actually reminds me a lot of the Rune Combiner in League of Legends. You have your basic crystals, ruby, sapphire, and emerald, and you can make combinations to create different gems and upgrade existing ones (ex. 3x rough ruby goes into tumbled ruby, 3x tumbled --> faceted, 3x faceted --> brilliant.) Each oculi gives a unique stat bonus depending on whether you put it on attack, defense, or time.Overall I give this game a 10/10. Buy this game!"
