,Recommended,256290,19382332,"Posted: 29 November, 2015",all,basement and chill,"There are so many beautiful aspects to Child of Light, although the combat system is nearly ruining the game for me. There's plenty of glowing reviews, so I'll focus on this one negative aspect in a short rant/review for anyone interested.So basically there's a feature which strips players of turns. I've played RPGs with somewhat similar mechanics, but here it  is what the outcome of a battle solely depends on. It's just frustrating. There's times where I almost think it's a brilliant idea. It adds something fresh to standard RPG gameplay, but ultimately it's flawed in my opinion. There's situations that you get into where it's a repeating cycle of trying to battle the turn setback, where you can't even manage to heal or defend, let alone fight the opponents at hand. At the beginning of the game it isn't detrimental, but it becomes very tedious a few hours in. You're combating a feature, not the enemies.Despite this, I would still recommend the game as a whole. There's so much brilliance to look forward to, and it could very well be my favorite title if it weren't for the feature discussed."
