76561197972140596,Recommended,256290,28864474,"Posted: 31 December, 2016",all,Kelso,"Child of Light received a lot of praise from critics and gamers alike for its unique approach to story-telling and graphics. While I enjoyed it, I wouldn't say I was quite as taken in as many seem to be.Its strongest points are undoubtedly it's unique visual aesthetic and beautiful piano-based soundtrack which perfectly matches the mood of the action on screen.It's fairy-tale story serves well enough, and I appreciate it for its attempt to be different, but at times the iambic pentameter rhyming was a little forced and somewhat tiresome.  It may be that I'm just not that crazy about turn-based combat, but I also found the combat in-game a little repetitive after 6-7 hours. From what I understand the turn-based combat in this game has more real-time elements than most turn-based games, but they weren't enough to really hook me on the moment to moment gameplay.Is this a good game worth playing? Absolutely. Is it a 9 or 10 out of 10 as many feel it is? In my opinion, no. What you get out of it will depend on your enjoyment of turn-based combat, your interest in a fairy-tale style story, and your appreciation of its beautiful hand-drawn graphics and elegant soundtrack.My overall rating: 7.5/10"
