,Recommended,256290,31313286,Posted: 22 April,all,SmartChimp,"I really enjoyed Child of Light.  At this time I have finished the game but have not collected all the collectables but have collected most of them and have completed pretty much all the quests.In terms of gameplay I found the combat engaging, it a turnbase system base with some real-time elements.  I found I was losing on the bosses and had to figure out a way to beat them.  There is always to option to grind a few levels if they do become to difficult to beat and I had to do that for a few of the later bosses but in general I felt I did not really have to grind in general.The story had my interest but was just a typical fairy tale-esque.  It is not challenging or thought provoking but it services the game well and flows well.  All the writing is in rhyme and I personally found it cute and neat but at some points some of the lines were stretching.  The characters themselves were a different then the typical trope characters found in fantasy RPGs.  The graphics and soundtrack are really great in this game and I think it was one of the things that kept me going to explore the world.The multiplayer/coop in the game seems to be more there to play with someone who isn't as familiar with RPGs than someone who you, I was thinking of playing this with a friend but when I tested it out I feel it would just be a frusterating experience for one of us.  I am not unhappy they have this in though, I think it's a nice feature, albeit one I didn't use.Overall, I felt this was a good game and a good introduction to turn-based JRPG mechanics."
