76561198007408164,Recommended,256290,35480271,Posted: 4 October,all,parrotd0x,"In short: beautiful and amazing game with small flaws.The biggest plusses are the master class art slyle, heartwarming music and lots of usable skills and companions. The inclusion of the light whisp is super cool!However, I didn't like some crucial things. The main story premise is nothing new and is also not served very well. Yet, the game could have made the player dive into it step by step while advancing (of all things the side story), but instead hecticly throws it around - you get too much of it, too fast.The 2nd thing is the actual combat: it's round based and works fairly well overall - if only some little obstacles were not around. Fully hit characters are interrupted in their attacks and have to pass on their current move, why is that? The combat mechanics with the light whisp also seem totally unnecessary and overloaded, which makes the fights turn into a mess of denying enemies, being interrupted, healing/reviving your buddies and maaaaaaaybe attacking one or two times.  It feels unsatisfying, I actually even tried to avoid smaller fights at some point. Less is more, isn't it?Also, why I'm bounded to install the god damned Uplay as well? Jesus..."
